In .NET MAUI, app lifecycle is handled through the `Window` class rather than `Application`. You subclass `Window` and override its lifecycle methods:

```csharp
public class App : Application
{
    protected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)
        => new MyWindow();
}

public class MyWindow : Window
{
    public MyWindow() : base(new MainPage()) { }

    protected override void OnCreated()    { /* was OnStart */ }
    protected override void OnStopped()    { /* was OnSleep */ }
    protected override void OnResumed()    { /* was OnResume */ }
    protected override void OnDestroying() { /* new: app closing */ }
}
```

**Mapping:**
| Xamarin.Forms | MAUI Window |
|---|---|
| `OnStart()` | `OnCreated()` |
| `OnSleep()` | `OnStopped()` / `OnDeactivated()` |
| `OnResume()` | `OnResumed()` / `OnActivated()` |

For platform-specific hooks, use `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in `MauiProgram.cs`:

```csharp
builder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>
{
#if ANDROID
    events.AddAndroid(android => android.OnStop(activity => { /* ... */ }));
#endif
});
```
